<span id="freeTextContainer11516863851162613008">It&apos;s an entertaining enough story, especially when one realizes that the old man is, potentially, an aging Sherlock Holmes (his name is never revealed). However, Chabon&apos;s introspective and ambulating writing style doesn&apos;t really lend itself to a detective story, slowing it down in places, even despite the book&apos;s length. There were a couple of sections where the spirit of Doyle&apos;s detective action were felt, but they were quickly overtaken by lengthier and denser passages.</span>
